  Measure.pi (wignerMeasureDist μ ν n)
```
where `wignerMeasureDist μ ν n` is a function from `Index n` (which is the same as `Fin n × Fin n` with `i ≤ j`) to `Measure ℝ`, such that:
- If `i = j` (diagonal entry), it returns `ν`
- If `i ≠ j` (off-diagonal entry), it returns `μ`

Since we're looking at the diagonal entry `i i`, the corresponding index in `WignerSpace n` is `⟨(i, i), by simp⟩`. The measure `WignerMeasure μ ν n` is the product measure where each coordinate has measure `μ` or `ν` depending on whether it's an off-diagonal or diagonal entry.

When we take the pushforward of `WignerMeasure μ ν n` through `fun ω ↦ (wignerMatrixMap n ω) i i`, we're essentially looking at the measure on the diagonal entry. Since the i-th diagonal entry in `WignerSpace n` is constructed with measure `ν` (as per `wignerMeasureDist`), the pushforward measure will also be ν.

