Now we need to prove this lemma. To do so, we need to show that the function `fun ω ↦ (wignerMatrixMap n ω) i i` (which extracts the i-th diagonal entry of the matrix) has the law ν with respect to the measure `WignerMeasure μ ν n`.

The definition of `WignerMeasure μ ν n` is `Measure.pi (wignerMeasureDist μ ν n)`, where `wignerMeasureDist μ ν n` is a function from `Index n` (which is the same as `Fin n × Fin n` with `i ≤ j`) to `Measure ℝ`, such that:
- If `i = j` (diagonal entry), it returns `ν`
- If `i ≠ j` (off-diagonal entry), it returns `μ`

When we take the pushforward of `WignerMeasure μ ν n` through `fun ω ↦ (wignerMatrixMap n ω) i i`, we're essentially looking at the measure on the diagonal entry. Since the i-th diagonal entry in `WignerSpace n` is constructed with measure `ν` (as per `wignerMeasureDist`), the pushforward measure will also be ν.

Now, formalizing this in Lean 4:

```tactics
